      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Home Section:</p>
        <p>Since the 1960's, my husband and I have discovered many "Treasures From the Trash" (Sept. 9), much to the embarrassment of our sons who had to stand by while we dug in the trash.</p>
        <p>We have lugged innumerable chairs home that needed to be caned, including an Eames-style chair from the International Center of Photography. Some of our finds were Italian ceramic tiles, an embossed folding screen (which a driver allowed us to carry on the bus), a steamer trunk that included the patents of an inventor and I think what may be the most unusual find, a wooden ox yoke with handmade nails found in a wire New York City trash can on East 84th Street.</p>
        <p>Our biggest fantasy is to own a van and drive up and down the streets looking for treasures. LOIS AND DAN EVANS  New York</p>
      </block>
